  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Feature request**\r\n\r\nCurrently we compute forkDataRoot every time we need to verify a signature. We could compute all `forkDataRoot`s for the known forks after genesis is known, and cache them.\r\n\r\nWe could even cache the domains as we compute them.\r\n\r\n**Proposal**\r\n\r\nExpose somewhere an interface like\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nexport interface IDomainCache {\r\n  getDomainAtSlot(domainType: DomainType, slot: Slot): Buffer;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**EDIT**: Note: I have not data to prove that this is an actual performance issue, it was just an idea that would be nice to de-duplicate work but maybe it has a negligible impact.\r\n\r\nOne may browse the issues with the performance label which are proven to have a serious impact on the node performance https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/labels/Performance",
