    "body": "it's worth to cache domains:\r\n```ts\r\nstate = generatePerfTestCachedBeaconState({goBackOneSlot: true});\r\n    const {config} = state;\r\n    let start = Date.now();\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10000; i++) {\r\n      state.blockRoots[100];\r\n    }\r\n    console.log(\"@@@ finish 10000 state.blockRoots[100] in\", Date.now() - start, \"ms\");\r\n    start = Date.now();\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10000; i++) {\r\n      state.slot;\r\n    }\r\n    console.log(\"@@@ finish 10000 state.slot in\", Date.now() - start, \"ms\");\r\n    start = Date.now();\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10000; i++) {\r\n      state.currentJustifiedCheckpoint.epoch;\r\n    }\r\n    console.log(\"@@@ finish 10000 state.currentJustifiedCheckpoint.epoch in\", Date.now() - start, \"ms\");\r\n    start = Date.now();\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10000; i++) {\r\n      getDomain(config, state, config.params.DOMAIN_BEACON_ATTESTER);\r\n    }\r\n    console.log(\"@@@ finish 10000 getDomain\", Date.now() - start, \"ms\");\r\n```\r\n```\r\n@@@ finish 10000 state.blockRoots[100] in 151 ms\r\n@@@ finish 10000 state.slot in 53 ms\r\n@@@ finish 10000 state.currentJustifiedCheckpoint.epoch in 173 ms\r\n@@@ finish 10000 getDomain 798 ms\r\n```\r\n\r\n`getDomain` is 5 times slower than `state.blockRoots` and caching block roots could save us 0.5s in epoch transition as in #2528",
